JAR and WAR
JAR - A JAR file is a package that contains compiled Java classes and resources bundled into one file.
myapp.jar
│
├── META-INF
│   └── MANIFEST.MF
│
├── com
│   └── example
│       └── MyClass.class
│
├── application.properties

WAR - A WAR file is a package specifically for web applications that runs inside a web server / application server.
myapp.war
│
├── index.jsp
├── css
├── js
│
└── WEB-INF
     ├── classes
     └── lib

Maven and few Java Commands
Maven
mvn -version -> To get the version of Maven we have in our system
mvn clean install -> To compile my desired accounts or loans any folder , Once it is done then it will create a JAR file

mvn clean install
→ Compiles the project
→ Runs tests
→ Packages the application

→ Generates JAR/WAR inside target folder That will create a JAR file
Then with the JAR file I will run
mvn spring-boot:run -> This will run accounts or selected folder as my spring boot application

